  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" State of Sikkim and Others versus Dr. Mool Raj Kotwal pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_4_2347_2363','2025INSC559'); ><font size='4'> <strong>STATE OF SIKKIM AND OTHERS<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>DR. MOOL RAJ KOTWAL </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 2347</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 559</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006982025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.K. MAHESHWARI<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, RAJESH BINDAL</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether an employee of the State who had availed the benefit of leave encashment maximum of 300 days once on attaining the age of superannuation under Rule 36 of Sikkim Government Services (Leave) Rules, 1982, can further be entitled for leave encashment again on relieving of re-employment. Headnotes&dagger; Sikkim Government Service Rules, 1974 &ndash; rr.98, 102 &ndash; Sikkim Government Services (Leave) Rules, 1982 &ndash; rr.6, 17, 31, 32, 36 &ndash; Grant of benefit of leave encashment second time for the period of re-employment of respondent after attaining<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 23-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 5464/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_4_2347_2363','2025INSC559','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div